restoreToken.description: Restore token used to differentiate soft-deleted objects with the same name and generation. Only applicable for hierarchical namespace buckets and if softDeleted is set to true. This parameter is optional, and is only required in the rare case when there are multiple soft-deleted objects with the same name and generation.

softDeleted.description: If true, only soft-deleted object versions will be listed. The default is false. For more information, see [Soft Delete](https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/soft-delete).

userProject.description: The project to be billed for this request. Required for Requester Pays buckets.

independent.description: Returns an IAM policy for the specified object.

generation.description: If present, selects a specific revision of this object (as opposed to the latest version, the default).

userProject.description: The project to be billed for this request. Required for Requester Pays buckets.

independent.description: Retrieves a list of objects matching the criteria.

delimiter.description: Returns results in a directory-like mode. items will contain only objects whose names, aside from the prefix, do not contain delimiter. Objects whose names, aside from the prefix, contain delimiter will have their name, truncated after the delimiter, returned in prefixes. Duplicate prefixes are omitted.

endOffset.description: Filter results to objects whose names are lexicographically before endOffset. If startOffset is also set, the objects listed will have names between startOffset (inclusive) and endOffset (exclusive).

filter.description: Filter the returned objects. Currently only supported for the contexts field. If delimiter is set, the returned prefixes are exempt from this filter.

includeFoldersAsPrefixes.description: Only applicable if delimiter is set to '/'. If true, will also include folders and managed folders (besides objects) in the returned prefixes.

includeTrailingDelimiter.description: If true, objects that end in exactly one instance of delimiter will have their metadata included in items in addition to prefixes.

matchGlob.description: Filter results to objects and prefixes that match this glob pattern.

maxResults.description: Maximum number of items plus prefixes to return in a single page of responses. As duplicate prefixes are omitted, fewer total results may be returned than requested. The service will use this parameter or 1,000 items, whichever is smaller.

pageToken.description: A previously-returned page token representing part of the larger set of results to view.

prefix.description: Filter results to objects whose names begin with this prefix.

projection.description: Set of properties to return. Defaults to noAcl.

softDeleted.description: If true, only soft-deleted object versions will be listed. The default is false. For more information, see [Soft Delete](https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/soft-delete).

startOffset.description: Filter results to objects whose names are lexicographically equal to or after startOffset. If endOffset is also set, the objects listed will have names between startOffset (inclusive) and endOffset (exclusive).

userProject.description: The project to be billed for this request. Required for Requester Pays buckets.

versions.description: If true, lists all versions of an object as distinct results. The default is false. For more information, see [Object Versioning](https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/object-versioning).

dependent.description: Starts asynchronous cancellation on a long-running operation. The server makes a best effort to cancel the operation, but success is not guaranteed.

Starts asynchronous advancement of the relocate bucket operation in the case of required write downtime, to allow it to lock the bucket at the source location, and proceed with the bucket location swap. The server makes a best effort to advance the relocate bucket operation, but success is not guaranteed.

independent.description: Gets the latest state of a long-running operation.
Lists operations that match the specified filter in the request.

filter.description: A filter to narrow down results to a preferred subset. The filtering language is documented in more detail in [AIP-160](https://google.aip.dev/160).

pageSize.description: Maximum number of items to return in a single page of responses. Fewer total results may be returned than requested. The service uses this parameter or 100 items, whichever is smaller.

pageToken.description: A previously-returned page token representing part of the larger set of results to view.
